HEADWORD: Mercurammonium
<hw>Mer`cur*am*mo"ni*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Mercur</ets>ic + <ets>ammonium</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A radical regarded as derived from ammonium by
the substitution of mercury for a portion of the hydrogen.</def>⟦br⟧
